Learn more by visiting the Help Center on our website.

node.text:
A common question we get asked is, "Why does my reticle appear blurry?"

Due to the nature of holographic technology, the 68MOA ring will appear to be comprised of thousands of little pixels. Unlike traditional scopes, the ring itself is not solid and will have the appearance of being fuzzy or pixilated. This is a normal phenomenon and one of the features of having a true holographic weapon sight.

Check out this video to learn more.

node.text:
The EOTECH Vudu 5-25x50mm Super Short is one of the shortest first-focal-plane rifle scopes ever made – with an awesome 5-25x magnification range and a host of enhancements to bring you closer than ever to downrange perfection. 

Its compact profile leaves room on your rail to adjust a thermal optic or night vision device without leaving the eyepiece. Packing unprecedented clarity and control thanks to razor-sharp high-definition (HD) glass and surgically precise turrets with our EZ Chek Zero Stop. Housed in a rugged, single-piece T6 aircraft-aluminum tube.

Specifications:
Product: EOTECH Vudu 5-25x50mm FFP
Magnification: 5-25x
Objective Lens: 50mm
Focal Plane: First
Overall Length: 11.2 inches
Weight: 29.5 ounces
Tube Diameter: 34mm
Adjustment Graduation: Windage/Elevation: 1 click = .1 MRAD
Eye Relief: 5x: 75-94 mm (2.96- 3.71 in), 25x: 83-92 mm (3.27 - 3.63 in)

node.text:
What’s happening in Afghanistan causes old wounds to be ripped opened. Feelings of hopelessness, devastation, and re-awakened grief pour out. To the men and women, and their families and friends, who sacrificed everything for the betterment of others—others who you didn’t even know, we thank you. You are heroes.

You are heroes to the men, women, and children of the United States and of Afghanistan—the people who could not (or would not) stand up for themselves and their freedom. You were strong when they couldn’t be. We’ve seen comments from vets saying they feel like their time was a waste. We are so sorry you feel this way. We truly hope you can find comfort in knowing that part of your legacy in this is showing others that it’s important to do the right thing in difficult situations. It’s important to stand up for others when they cannot stand up for themselves; you are the heroes that have set the example for future generations.

If you are feeling hopeless and grieving during this time, please reach out to someone- anyone. Tell them how you feel. Your life is meaningful, and your anger and/or sadness is valid and shared by many. Thank you for your service. We love you.

Photo credit: @n_betts
